<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1208,1487]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,390,1280,1307]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Verrill" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[398,631,1280,1306]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" genus="Bunodosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="grande">
<emphasis box="[398,631,1280,1306]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Bunodosoma grande</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the intertidal zone to about 
<quantity box="[1047,1091,1280,1307]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" unit="m" value="5.0">5 m</quantity>
deep, abundant in the shallow subtidal. Subtidal individuals can be found on exposed surfaces, occasionally surrounded by encrusting sponges (
<bibRefCitation author="Fautin, D. G. &amp; Hickman, C. P. &amp; Daly, M. &amp; Molodtsova, T." box="[159,363,1352,1379]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="549 - 573" refId="ref13855" refString="Fautin, D. G., Hickman, C. P., Daly, M. &amp; Molodtsova, T. (2007) Shallow-water sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniaria) and tube anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Ceriantharia) of the Galapagos Islands. Pacific Science, 61 (4), 549 - 573. https: // doi. org / 10.2984 / 1534 - 6188 (2007) 61 [549: SSACAA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2007">
Fautin 
<emphasis box="[239,288,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen collected in Magdalena Bay was found attached to a mangrove trunk.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
